channel.title: Strange file
channel.description:
Well, I found thise folder in my D: and I didnt know what it was for. The folder is named c8edc2d25ea17a27eb and all it contains is a text document called msxml4-KB927978-enu. What the hell is this? Is it something bad or is it not :confused:. It contains stuff like this:
[code]MSI (s) (74:AC) [18:14:26:281]: Machine policy value 'DisableUserInstalls' is 0 MSI (s) (74:AC) [18:14:26:390]: File will have security applied from OpCode. MSI (s) (74:AC) [18:14:26:718]: SOFTWARE RESTRICTION POLICY: Verifying package --> 'd:\c8edc2d25ea17a27eb\msxml.msi' against software restriction policy MSI (s) (74:AC) [18:14:26:718]: SOFTWARE RESTRICTION POLICY: d:\c8edc2d25ea17a27eb\msxml.msi has a digital signature MSI (s) (74:AC) [18:14:27:171]: SOFTWARE RESTRICTION POLICY: d:\c8edc2d25ea17a27eb\msxml.msi is permitted to run at the 'unrestricted' authorization level. MSI (s) (74:AC) [18:14:27:187]: End dialog not enabled MSI (s) (74:AC) [18:14:27:187]: Original package ==> d:\c8edc2d25ea17a27eb\msxml.msi MSI (s) (74:AC) [18:14:27:187]: Package we're running from ==> C:\WINDOWS\Installer\a9fefb.msi MSI (s) (74:AC) [18:14:27:218]: APPCOMPAT: looking for appcompat database entry with ProductCode '{37477865-A3F1-4772-AD43-AAFC6BCFF99F}'.[/code]

item.title: Strange file
item.dc:creator: @Javacisnotrecognized _^_
item.description:
@Javacisnotrecognized wrote:

No, thats part of the FAT32 filing system. They inhererted the strange names from FAT (File Allocation Table) . Also, your file in particular in an installation log, so incase you ever install the thing that made that log, it can be uninstalled correctly.

Read full topic
